\pard\s1\sb240\sa120{\b\fs44 {\rtlch\f1 \b \cf2 \fs28 Structural Elements\b0 }}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 Miscellaneous structural elements you can add to your document, like footnotes, endnotes, dropcaps and the like. }\par
\pard\s2\sb240\sa120{\b\fs40 {\rtlch\f1 \b \cf3 \fs26 Footnotes & Endnotes\b0 }}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 Footnotes}\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs20  In paged media, footnotes are usually displayed at the bottom of the text. However, in ebooks, a better paradigm is to make them clickable endnotes that the user can browse at her pleasure. This conversion is handled automatically by calibre.}\par
{\rtlch\f1  and endnotes}\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs20  Endnotes are typically used for longer notes, they remain endnotes when converted into ebook form, except that they have an additional backlink to make it easy to return to the current position after reading the note.}\par
{\rtlch\f1  are automatically recognized and both are converted to endnotes, with backlinks for maximum ease of use in ebook devices.}\par
\pard\s2\sb240\sa120{\b\fs40 {\rtlch\f1 \b \cf3 \fs26 Dropcaps\b0 }}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs116 D}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 rop}{\rtlch\f1  caps are used to emphasize the leading paragraph at the start of a section. In }{\rtlch\f1 Word}{\rtlch\f1  it is possible to s}{\rtlch\f1 p}{\rtlch\f1 ecify how many lines of text a drop-cap should use.}\par
\pard\s2\sb240\sa120{\b\fs40 {\rtlch\f1 \b \cf3 \fs26 Links\b0 }}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 Two kinds of links are possible, those that refer to an external website and those that refer to }{\rtlch\f1 locations}{\rtlch\f1  inside the document itself. Both are supported by calibre. For example, here is a link pointing to the }{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://calibre-ebook.com/download"}}{\fldrslt {\rtlch\f1 \ul \cf12 calibre download page\ul0 }}}{\rtlch\f1 .}{\rtlch\f1  Then we have a link that points back to the section on }{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "#_Paragraph_level_formatting"}}{\fldrslt {\rtlch\f1 \ul \cf12 paragraph level formatting\ul0 }}}{\rtlch\f1  in this document.}\par
\pard\s2\sb240\sa120{\b\fs40 {\rtlch\f1 \b \cf3 \fs26 Table of Contents\b0 }}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1  You can see the}{\rtlch\f1  Table of Contents}{\rtlch\f1  created by calibre}{\rtlch\f1  by clicking the Table of Contents button in whatever viewer you are using to view the converted ebook.}{\rtlch\f1  }\par
